# Gyumri Tour Guide Bot - Improvement Ideas

Based on my review of the current codebase and your request, here is the plan for migrating to the new OpenStreetMap data source ([openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py)).

## 1. Migrate to OpenStreetMap Data Source (High Priority)
The user has decided to switch from the OpenTripMap data source ([places_gyumri.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/places_gyumri.json) and [places_gyumri_mvp.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/places_gyumri_mvp.json)) to the new OpenStreetMap data source generated by [openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py). The new JSON structure is different from the old one, and the codebase needs to be updated.
- **[data_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py):** Update the data loading logic to point to [openstreetmap/gyumri_places.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/gyumri_places.json). Modify the helper functions like [get_nearby_places](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py#54-92) to properly parse the new data structure (the `tags` dictionary instead of the old flat structure). We need to map OSM properties into our internal `Point of Interest` dictionary safely.
- **[routing.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/routing.py):** Update the routing logic to categorize places using OSM tags (e.g. `tourism=attraction`, `amenity=restaurant`) instead of the old OTM categories. Update name extraction (e.g., trying `tags["name:ru"]`, `tags["name:en"]`, then fallback to `name`).
- **[llm.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/llm.py):** Modify how context from nearby places is formatted for the LLM to understand the new OSM structure.

## 2. Database Persistence for User State (Medium Priority)
The bot provides text descriptions of tourist places but lacks visuals and audio appeal.
- **Photos:** The `photo_urls` field in places data is currently empty. We can enhance [build_db.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/build_db.py) to fetch image URLs from OpenTripMap or Wikipedia API and use `message.answer_photo` when sending place navigation cards.
- **Audio Guides:** We can integrate a Text-to-Speech API (like OpenAI TTS) to convert textual descriptions into voice messages so tourists can listen while walking the city without looking at their phones constantly.

## 3. Dynamic LLM-Powered Routing (Medium Priority)
Currently, [routing.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/routing.py) uses hardcoded rule-based logic to select places depending entirely on distance and rudimentary categories (Classic, Food, Chill).
- **Solution:** Pass the nearby places and the user's specific text preferences directly to the LLM (DeepSeek/Groq), prompting it to compute and dynamically construct a context-aware route sequence tailored specifically to the user's exact interests.

## 4. Gamification & Progression (Low Priority)
To make the tour more engaging for tourists:
- Add a "Tourist Passport" system where users collect stamps/achievements for visited locations in Gyumri.
- Integrate simple trivia quizzes about Gyumri's history as the user checks into locations along the route.

## 5. Deployment Readiness (Easy)
- Add a `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` file to package the application and make it trivial to deploy on a VPS server.

> [!TIP]
> Let me know which of these ideas you want to prioritize or if you have another feature in mind!
